section.section:
This section does not apply to a bond that:
matures within 1 year after the date of issue and is issued:
in anticipation of tax receipts;
to meet current expenses; or
to meet an emergency;
is sold to the United States or a unit or instrumentality of the United States;
is issued under a plan of composition approved in a proceeding under Chapter IX of the United States Bankruptcy Act; or
is issued under any other plan to refund or refinance in exchange, bond for bond, an outstanding maturing debt, other than:
a current or floating debt; or
a bond under item (i) of this paragraph.

The notice shall:
be in the form required in the resolution that authorizes the issuance of the bonds;
state the date, time, and place of the public sale;
describe the bonds by reference to the enabling act under which they are authorized;
state the date of issue;
state the total principal amount;
state the schedule of maturities;
state the interest payable or the manner of determining the interest;
state the purpose for which the proceeds will be used;
describe the general form of the bonds, including:
whether the bonds will be in coupon or registered form; and
whether the principal or interest or both will be registrable;
state that each bid must be made in writing by sealed proposal; and
state the amount of the good faith deposit that the State unit has determined must accompany the bid.
